      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> – this is your<strong> aioli</strong></p>",
